text: Cumia brazieri is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colubrariidae, the spindle snails, the tulip snails and their allies. ==Description== The shell size is up to 70 mm ==Distribution== This species occurs off Queensland and New South Wales, Australia ==References== ==External links== * Category:Colubrariidae Category:Gastropods of Australia Category:Gastropods described in 1869
title: Cumia brazieri
